cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is a survey on machine reading comprehension systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the structures and approaches of machine reading comprehension systems, which involves machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pre-trained embeddings, which is related to representation learning and could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
